      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios; at minimum two distinct load configurations or displacement rates evaluated.",
      "rationale": "All validation testing was conducted under a single standardized ASTM F1717 configuration at a fixed crosshead displacement rate of 5 mm/min. While ASTM F1717 is the regulatory standard for spinal implant mechanical testing and the protocol was rigorously controlled, only one test condition was evaluated. Engineering judgment supports that the standard protocol is representative of worst-case static loading; however, no supplementary load configurations or displacement rates were included in the validation dataset. The team considers this a conservative, well-characterized condition appropriate for the intended regulatory submission context."
    },
    {
